verbose_text: RANKL secreted by osteoblasts can bind with RANK in osteoclast precursors to upregulate expression of NFATc1, which is critical for osteoclast differentiation, via TRAF6 to initiate the downstream NF-kappaB signal pathway [XREF_BIBR].
